<li id="cite_note-Lucas-67"><span class="mw-cite-backlink" id="mwC70"><a href="#cite_ref-Lucas_67-0" id="mwC74"><span class="mw-linkback-text" id="mwC78">1 </span></a><a href="#cite_ref-Lucas_67-1" id="mwC8A"><span class="mw-linkback-text" id="mwC8E">2 </span></a><a href="#cite_ref-Lucas_67-2" id="mwC8I"><span class="mw-linkback-text" id="mwC8M">3 </span></a><a href="#cite_ref-Lucas_67-3" id="mwC8Q"><span class="mw-linkback-text" id="mwC8U">4 </span></a><a href="#cite_ref-Lucas_67-4" id="mwC8Y"><span class="mw-linkback-text" id="mwC8c">5 </span></a></span> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-Lucas-67" class="mw-reference-text reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFLucas" class="citation web cs1">Lucas, Stephen E. <a href="https://www.archives.gov/exhibits/charters/declaration_style.html" class="external text external" id="mwC8k">"The Stylistic Artistry of the Declaration of Independence"</a>. National Archives and Records Administration. <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20120630232450/http://www.archives.gov/exhibits/charters/declaration_style.html" class="external text external" id="mwC8s">Archived</a> from the original on June 30, 2012<span class="reference-accessdate" id="mwC8w">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap" id="mwC80">July 4,</span> 2012</span>.</cite></span></li>
